                        Stuart
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d823</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">823</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-11-28T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-11-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-11-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="823" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d823">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0093/11–2848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-11-28">November 28,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received November 28—11:16 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2348. For ComNavWesPac. Final arrangements completed Manila for accommodation
                    Embassy consular dependents. Please arrange airlift Nanking group beginning
                    Thursday, December 2 and Shanghai group soon as possible thereafter. Will notify
                    you November 29 exact number desiring airlift as number somewhat lower than that
                    given you previously.</p>
                <p>Sent Tsingtao 218; repeated Shanghai 1170, Manila 40, Hankow 64, Department 2348,
                    Peiping 248.</p>
                <p>Shanghai pass to CTF 78.<note n="80" xml:id="d823fn80">Commander Task Force
                        78.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
